# Open With Background Layers

This is a GIMP Script that opens a new image with two blank layers underneath (1 black and 1 white)

## Install

The installation process is straightforward. To install the plugin, please follow these steps:

* Save the plugin `.scm` to your local drive.
* Open GIMP and navigate to `Edit > Preferences > Folders > Scripts` to find the name of the folder your GIMP installation will look for scripts.
* Using Windows Explorer copy the `.scm` file to GIMPâ€™s Scripts folder.
* Restart GIMP or go to `Filters > Script-Fu > Refresh Scripts` .
* Once installed, the plugin will be available under the "Plugins" menu in GIMP.


